1. --
{ Alright! A little informational variation is in order to explain what is meant with the 'Réti Gambit' throughout this course. This name is usually attributed to a completely different position, namely   1.e4  e6  2.b3!?  d5  3.Bb2?!  which, while certainly a fresh and interesting try, has nothing to do with this course!  In this course, the term 'Réti Gambit' will be used to describe the gambit arising after   1.Nf3  d5  c4!?  which bears some resemblance to the Queen's Gambit, but is still a very different opening, especially due to moves like  d4!?  being possible for Black.  This gambit will be explored in much more detail in the two first theoretical chapters, namely Réti Gambit: Accepted and Réti Gambit: Declined, so no need to worry! All your questions will be answered very soon!  I hope this clears up any confusion as to what the 'Réti Gambit' means in context of this course and I hope you'll enjoy learning about this particular gambit in the Réti! }
