1. Nf3 d5 2. c4
{ This is the starting point of our analysis in this chapter, excluding 2... dxc4. }
2... d4
{ This is 'The Ambitious' variation, which is played around 20% of the time in this position.   2...c6  e3  This is 'The Slav' variation, which is played around 15% of the time in this position. This continuation is covered in the9th,10th,11th and12th variation.   2...e6  e3  This is 'The French' variation, which is played around 12% of the time in this position. This continuation is covered in the13th and14th variation.   2...Nf6  cxd5  This is 'The Conservative' variation, which is played around 12% of the time in this position. This continuation is covered in the15th,16th,17th and18th variation. }
3. e3
{ This will give us good fighting positions, which is supported by a 55% winrate. }
3... c5
{ This move is played around 36% of the time.   3...dxe3  fxe3  This continuation is played around 35% of the time and is covered in the5th and6th variation.   3...d3  Ne5  This continuation is played around 19% of the time and is covered in the7th variation.   3...Nc6  exd4  This continuation is played around 8% of the time and is covered in the8th variation. }
4. b4 b6
{ This move is played around 45% of the time.   4...dxe3  fxe3  This continuation is played around 22% of the time and is covered in the2nd and3rd variation.   4...e6  bxc5  This continuation is played around 12% of the time and is covered in the4th variation. }
5. bxc5 bxc5 6. Nxd4 cxd4 7. Qf3 dxe3 8. fxe3 Nc6 9. Qxc6+ Bd7 10. Qf3
{ This is the variation with all the most played moves and is explained in detail in the1st variation. }
