[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "2 - Réti Gambit Declined - 1... d5"]
[Black "Introduction to Chapter"]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 d5 2. c4
{ All the moves so far have been explained in the 'Introduction to 1... d5' in the introduction chapter.  Introduction to 1... d5 }
2... d4
{ Welcome to the second chapter regarding the 1... d5 reply from Black, more specifically, the Réti Gambit: Declined.  Our opponent declines our "pawn-sacrifice" and instead grabs more space in the center and prevents us from capturing on d5.  Objectively speaking, this is the best way to continue for Black, but it can be difficult to play and our opponent is very unlikely to be comfortable in these positions.  We will apply a ton of pressure, outprepare our opponent and reap the rewards! }
3. e3
{ The same move as after dxc4, but with different ideas.  We prepare to simply win the d4 pawn  (if Black ignores our threat)  and also prepare to recapture with our f-pawn - if Black captures our pawn - giving us a great center with active play.  There's a few common responses from Black here, but the ones that are mostly played at the lower level grant us great chances. This is supported by a 56% winrate in this position. }
