7... Qxb3
{ Doubling White's pawns, not allowing us to double theirs and releasing the tension between the queens. }
8. axb3 Bd7 9. d4
{ White is simply doing very well here. The Black bishop on d7 is looking extremely passive, White's doubled-pawns aren't much of a weakness due to the active rook on a1 and White's bishops have many options to get very active due to White's big space advantage.  We will often look to play f3 and Kf2, to fully consolidate our killer center. Once Black has developed their b8 knight, we will also often look to capture on d7 to gain the bishop pair. We're clearly in the driver's seat! }
