{ Since Black has ideas of Bb4  (which we will almost exclusively meet with a3, when our knight is on c3)  we will try to get them to transpose to a familiar position with d5 and Nf6 first. }
5... Nf6 6. e3 { We've almost transposed. } 6... Bb4+
{ An interesting move, as now 7. Nc3 wouldn't be good due to Nd5 } 7. Nbd2
{ While our knight is now on d2 instead of c3, that doesn't change our plans much. It's also not clear what Black gains from not playing d5, surely, that's where the d-pawn belongs!?  Look to play a3 as soon as possible - just like if our knight was on c3  (within reason, don't do it if Black plays Nh5 before moving your bishop, for example!)   We will look to play the aforementioned a3, Bd3, Bg5, h3 and O-O with a good position. }
