1. Nf3 Nc6 2. d4 d5 3. c4 dxc4 4. d5 Nb4
{ This is just a game-losing blunder by Black.  Can you spot the winning blow? It's very thematic.  This tactic is also covered in the variation below  4 - Mikenas Defense - The Simple 2.. d5 with 3.. dxc4 }
5. Qa4+ { Well done! } 5... c6
{ Doesn't matter what Black plays here, the knight can't be saved. } 6. Qxb4
{ Very nice!  Statistically speaking, this blunder is played by Black around 40% of the time, so it's important to know this! }
