[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 Nc6 2. d4 d5 3. c4 dxc4 4. d5 Nb8 5. e4 e6 6. Bxc4 exd5 7. Bxd5 c6
{ This move is a blunder and allows White to gain a winning position.  Can you spot the winning move?  This continuation is also mentioned in the variation  1 - Mikenas Defense - The Simple 2... d5 with 3... dxc4 }
8. Bxf7+ { Great find! } 8... Ke7
{ Not   8...Kxf7??  Qxd8  Where White is up a queen! } 9. Qb3
{ Nicely done!  Black's king is in the middle of the board and White is threatening all sorts of things, for example, Bxg8 if Black doesn't move the knight. }
