[Black "Puzzle #17"]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 c5 2. c3 d6
{ This move wasn't covered in the theory chapter, but was quickly mentioned in the informational variationIntroduction to chapter.  Play the thematic follow-up! }
3. d4
{ Very good! Since we've played both c3 and Nf3, we want to use that to break through with d4! }
3... cxd4
{ Why else play the Sicilian? 4. dxc5 and 5. Qxd8 was also a threat. } 4. cxd4
{ Well done! Here Black's best response is 4... d5, simply admitting to their mistake of putting the pawn on d6, as our knight and pawn are both controlling e5, making the d6 pawn look dumb, and we have the threat of 5. e4.  White is already better! }
