[White "Puzzles"]
[Black "Puzzle #18"]
[Result "*"]

1. Nf3 c5 2. c3 d5 3. d4 Nc6 4. dxc5 a5
{ This ambitious move for Black doesn't work and was mentioned in the variation1 - Réti Sicilian - 2... d5 & 3... Nc6.  Do you remember what to play? }
5. e4 { A brilliant shot! White will capture on d5 if allowed. } 5... dxe4 6.
Qxd8+ Nxd8 7. Ne5
{ Nicely done! We're preparing to play Bb5+, which would trade everything off and hang onto our c5 pawn. We also don't need to rush and can start with a move like Na3.  Black will lose castling rights after we trade and will also have a hard time developing their dark-squared bishop and defending the pawn on e4. White is significantly better. }
