1. Nf3 f5 2. e4 fxe4 3. Ng5 Nf6 4. d3 exd3 5. Bxd3 d5
{ This move allows us to strike with our thematic capture and open up the light squares around the Black king.  Can you find the move? }
6. Bxh7
{ Well done! I hope you also saw what to do after the knight captures. } 6...
Nxh7 7. Qh5+ { A great move! } 7... Kd7 8. Nf7 Nf6 9. Qxh8
{ Very well done! In this position there was no mate on d5, due to Black's knight on f6, and Black will therefore be able to save their queen for the cost of an exchange.  The Black king is still on d7 though and completely blocking the queenside pieces, meaning White still has a winning position. }
