{ This will be a model game showcasing our main line of Réti Gambit: Accepted 1... d5 & 2... dxc4.  The game was a 3+0 rated game played in June 2021 on lichess. }
1. Nf3 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e3 b5 4. a4 c6 5. axb5 cxb5 6. Nc3 Bd7 7. Ne5 Nf6 8.
Qf3
{ This is explained in detail in the variation1 - The Overambitious 3... b5, where we concluded a big White advantage. Let's see how the game went on! }
8... Nc6 { Giving up the knight to save the rook. } 9. Nxc6 Bxc6 10. Qxc6+ Nd7
{ Not   10...Qd7??  Qxa8! } 11. Nxb5 { Black can safely resign. } 11... f6 12.
Nc7+ Kf7 { This allows mate in 7 by White. } 13. Nxa8
{ White instead picks up the rook, which is obviously also completely winning. }
13... Kg8 { This, yet again, runs into mate. } 14. Qd5+
{ 14.Qe6#  Would have been one move faster. } 14... e6 15. Qxe6#
{ And just like that, Black got mated only 7 moves after the position where our analysis ended!  A great example of how to keep the pressure up and drive the full point home, from the winning position reached in our theory. }
