[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "Student Games"]
[Black "QuantumJoe (2080) vs. goursundor (2106)"]
[Result "*"]

{ This will be a model game showcasing our main line of Réti Sicilian: 1... c5 & 2... Nc6.  The game was a 3+0 rated Blitz game played on lichess. }
1. Nf3 c5 2. c3 Nc6 3. d4 cxd4 4. cxd4 d5 5. Bf4
{ All the moves so far have been explained in detail in the variation1 - Réti Sicilian - The Solid 2... Nc6 & 4... d5. }
5... Bf5
{ In the aforementioned variations we looked at this position with Nc3 and Nf6 played, but the idea stays the same. }
6. Qb3
{ Thematic and strong, more or less forcing the rare Na5! for full equality. }
6... e6 { This doesn't work. } 7. Qxb7 Rc8
{ This move doesn't make much sense, but I think it was played because Black missed that they could get their bishop out and defend their knight adequately with  7...Bb4+!  8.Nc3  Nge7!  where White is still better, but not winning as after the text move. }
8. Nc3
{ White's extra pawn and better pieces are enough for a winning advantage already, but there's still play. }
8... Bb4 9. e3 { Just preparing to get the bishop to b5. } 9... Nf6
{ Now this could technically have arisen through the aforementioned variation, as our knight is on c3 and Black's knight is on f6.  Also, this is a horrible move, as now Bb5 hits extremely hard. The knight was definitely needed on e7. }
10. Bb5 O-O { Black has no way to save the piece. } 11. Bxc6
{ Now White's a piece up and it's just a matter of technique. } 11... Ne4 12.
Qxb4 { Trading pieces, which we love doing when we're ahead. } 12... Rxc6 13.
O-O Rb6 14. Qa3 Nxc3 15. bxc3 { Yum, more trades! } 15... Qc8 16. Ne5 Qb7 17.
c4 dxc4 18. Nxc4 Ra6 19. Qb3 Qd5 20. Nd2 Qa5 21. Nf3 Rb6 22. Qc4 Be4 23. Ne5
Bd5 24. Qe2 Rc8 25. Qh5 g6 26. Qh6 f6 27. Ng4 Rf8 28. Bc7 Qb5 29. Bxb6 Qxb6 30.
Rab1 Qc6 31. Nxf6+ Rxf6 32. Rb8+ Kf7 33. Qf8#
{ Checkmate! A beautiful game to illustrate how to punish Black for an inappropriate reaction to our thematic ideas connected to Qb3 and a clean conversion from there.  Thank you for your game submission QuantumJoe and congratulations on getting another game picked for the chapter! :D }
